A disk image represents the content exactly as it is on the original storage decive, including both data and structure information 
on the disk. It's a hard drive that may be saved as a virtual hard disk.


A disk parition is splitting up the hard drive memory; all the imaginary sections of the hard drive. 


The are many imaginary sections in the hard drive. 

It doesn't know what to mount unless you are very specfic with your mounting.

There are many steps in the this processs to mounting a disk image.

